etary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many hen harrier nests there were on (a) RSPB and (b) non-RSPB reserves in each of the last six years; how many of those nests failed to have any chicks fledge; and what the causes of each of those nest failures were.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan","203413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027697","Home Office","false","2019-01-28","<p>The continued safety and security of both UK and EU citizens remains our top priority.</p><p>That is why we are preparing for all eventualities – including a no deal scenario in which the current mechanisms we use to cooperate with EU Member States are not available when we exit the EU in March 2019.</p><p>The alternative arrangements for the EU ‘tools’ in question would include making more use of Interpol, Council of Europe Conventions and other forms of cooperation with European partners, such as bilateral channels</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-01-28T11:36:07.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027697/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027697/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027697/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-12-18","EU Justice and Home Affairs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans the Government has for alternative arrangements for (a) Schengen Information System II, (b) European Arrest Warrant, (c) European Criminal Records Information System, (d) Europol, (e) Eurojust  and (f) European Investigation Orders in the event of the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","203414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027698","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-21","<p>There is work underway to review the service specifications for children and young people with cancer. This will provide an opportunity to consider how some aspects of the patient pathway may be provided more locally to reduce the travel burden for patients and their families.</p><p> </p><p>Currently the Healthcare Travel Costs Scheme which is part of the NHS Low Income Scheme allows for patients (and in certain circumstances their carers) to receive reimbursement of travel if they are in receipt of a qualifying benefit or on a low income. The NHS Low Income Scheme has helped 337,000 applicants to receive financial help with their National Health Service treatment.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-12-21T14:10:40.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027698/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027698/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027698/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-12-18","Cancer: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if his Department will establish a Young Cancer Patient Travel Fund to cover the costs of travel to and from hospital for cancer treatment appointments for children, young people and their families.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","203415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027699","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-12-27","<p>The Office for Product Safety and Standards is undertaking a review of the actions taken by Whirlpool in relation to its modification programme and we will report to the House in due course.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-12-27T13:20:34.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027699/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027699/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027699/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-12-18","Whirlpool Corporation: Tumble Dryers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy,  with reference to the January 2017 enforcement notice issued by Peterborough Trading Standards, what steps the Office for Product Safety and Standards has taken to ensure that Whirlpool (a) identifies and (b) repairs the estimated one million fire-risk dryers in homes.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","203283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027700","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-12-27","<p>The Office for Product Safety and Standards is undertaking a review of the actions taken by Whirlpool in relation to its modification programme and we will report to the House in due course.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-12-27T13:20:54.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027700/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027700/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027700/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-12-18","Whirlpool Corporation: Tumble Dryers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what information his Department holds on the incidence of Whirlpool tumble dryer modifications being deployed incorrectly in machines manufactured (a) between April 2004 and September 2015 and (b) machines manufactured after September 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","203284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027701","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-20","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-12-20T16:07:31.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027701/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027701/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027701/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-12-18","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) inaccurate maintenance assessments and (b) incorrect maintenance adjustments were made to Child Support Agency schemes in (i) 1993 and (ii) 2003; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","Hemel Hempstead","Sir Mike Penning","203285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027702","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-20","<p>£3,506 million is owned in cash terms in Child Support Agency scheme arrears. This is all arrears including Child Support Agency arrears that have already been transitioned to the Child Maintenance Service.</p><p> </p><p>This figure is published as part of the ‘1993 and 2003 Child Maintenance Schemes – Client Funds Account 2017/18’ which can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-maintenance-client-funds-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-maintenance-client-funds-accounts</a></p><p />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-12-20T15:42:35.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027702/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027702/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027702/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-12-18","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much in cash terms is owed in Child Support Agency schemes arrears.","false","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","Hemel Hempstead","Sir Mike Penning","203286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027703","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-20","<p>As write off of Child Support Agency schemes arrears began in April 2012, there is not yet 10 years of data available.</p><p /><p>Between April 2012 and March 2013 £1,133,000 was written off in Child Support Agency arrears.</p><p> </p><p>The amount written off in Child Support Agency arrears has been published for each year since April 2013 - March 2014 as part of the Child Maintenance: Client Fund Accounts which can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-maintenance-client-funds-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-maintenance-client-funds-accounts</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-12-20T15:17:11.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027703/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027703/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027703/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-12-18","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much in cash terms has been written off in Child Support Agency schemes arrears in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","Hemel Hempstead","Sir Mike Penning","203287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027704","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Washington and Sunderland West (Mrs Sharon Hodgson) on 13 December 2018 to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-12-06/199808/" target="_blank">199808</a>.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-01-07T13:39:12.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027704/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027704/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027704/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-12-18","Human Papillomavirus: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if his Department will implement a catch-up programme of HPV vaccination for adolescent boys aged 14 to 18 to ensure that group is effectively protected.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","203416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027705","Department for International Development","false","2018-12-21","<p>The UK has led the international response, including using our role at the UN Security Council to push for international accountability and long-term support for the Rohingya. The UK government is supporting Rohingya in Bangladesh, as well as pushing for improved conditions in Rakhine State in order to allow voluntary, safe and dignified returns, with UNHCR oversight. We have been one of the main donors to the international humanitarian joint response plan and we expect to remain a leading donor.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-12-21T15:29:14.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027705/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027705/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027705/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-12-18","Rohingya: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to promote a long-term solution for Rohingya refugees.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","203417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027706","Department for International Development","false","2018-12-21","<p>We continue to discuss the status of the Rohingya with the government of Bangladesh, which prefers not to formally recognise them as refugees. We maintain that refugee status would help to ensure appropriate support and security for the Rohingya. It would also help with raising the urgent funds needed from the international community.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-12-21T15:29:47.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027706/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027706/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027706/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-12-18","Bangladesh: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions her Department has had with the Government of Bangladesh on granting refugee status to the Rohingya.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","203418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027707","Department for International Development","false","2018-12-21","<p>Congestion remains a serious challenge for the Rohingya refugee response and we have encouraged the government of Bangladesh at the highest levels to make more onshore land available. Bangladesh has already provided some additional land and the UK has supported international efforts to make this suitable and safe. We have made clear that any relocation of refugees must be safe, dignified and meet international humanitarian principles and standards.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-12-21T15:28:28.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027707/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027707/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027707/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-12-18","Bangladesh: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions her Department has had with the Government of Bangladesh on providing additional flat and usable land for Rohingya refugees.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","203419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027708","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-07","<p>We are working with countries across the world to ensure the UK remains a global leader in free trade as we leave the EU. This year’s Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting in London saw leaders adopt a six-point Connectivity Agenda for Trade and Investment to boost intra-Commonwealth trade to $2 Trillion by 2030. We are also currently working towards developing our overall approach to potential future trade negotiations, including with respect to government procurement, and our public consultations continue to will help to inform this.</p><p>Government is required to award contracts through fair and open competition in line with international obligations, which ensures value for money for the taxpayer. We will use opportunities offered by our exit from the EU to carefully consider longer-term options for the UK’s public procurement rules.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-01-07T17:17:34.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027708/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027708/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027708/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-12-18","Overseas Trade: Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the merits of targets for increased procurement from Commonwealth nations after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","203420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027709","Treasury","false","2019-01-07","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) published estimates of potential impacts of the new treatment on the deficit in their October 2018 Economic and fiscal outlook, which is available here: https://obr.uk/box/accounting-for-student-loans/</p><p> </p><p>However, the Office for National Statistics (ONS) has made it clear that there is a lot to decide before their methodology is finalised. The ONS currently aim to fully implement the new treatment for student loans in the public sector finances in September 2019.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2019-01-07T14:23:44.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027709/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027709/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027709/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-12-18","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the amount by which the deficit will increase in 2018 as a result of the ONS decision on the treatment of student loans in Government accounts.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","203421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027710","Department for International Trade","false","2018-12-21","<p>All UK companies from any region can participate in the Department for International Trade’s (DIT) supported events at trade shows. We advertise events on Event Hub on GREAT.gov.uk and through our international trade advisers who are based across the country, including the North East.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the North East benefits from participation in the specific DIT Northern Powerhouse (NPH) trade missions programme. The DIT North East team work closely with northern organisations and the UK’s global HMG network to assist companies who are participating in any trade mission, either NPH or national.</p><p> </p><p>We do not intend to place a map of the UK on trade show stands.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","203424","2018-12-21T15:34:29.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027710/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027710/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027710/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-12-18","Trade Fairs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 20 November 2018 to Question 191411, what recent steps his Department has taken to ensure that every region of the UK is represented in his Department’s trade show stands.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","203422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027711","Department for Education","false","2019-01-07","<p>The Office for National Statistics (ONS) announced a new treatment of student loans in the public sector finances and national accounts on 17 December 2018. The decision by the ONS relates to the recording of student loans in the national accounts and public sector finances. Prior to the announcement of the ONS review, the government had already launched the Review of Post-18 Education and Funding in which, amongst other features of the system, funding is being considered.</p><p> </p><p>The review is considering how to ensure that the education system for those aged 18 years and over is accessible to all, is supported by a funding system that provides value for money and works for students and taxpayers. In addition, the review is considering how the education system incentivises choice and competition across the sector and encourages the development of the skills that we need as a country.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-01-07T15:17:34.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027711/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027711/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027711/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-12-18","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will ensure that the level of funding allocated to universities is not reduced as a result of the ONS decision on the treatment of student loans in Government accounts.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","203423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027712","Department for International Trade","false","2018-12-21","<p>All UK companies from any region can participate in the Department for International Trade’s (DIT) supported events at trade shows. We advertise events on Event Hub on GREAT.gov.uk and through our international trade advisers who are based across the country, including the North East.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the North East benefits from participation in the specific DIT Northern Powerhouse (NPH) trade missions programme. The DIT North East team work closely with northern organisations and the UK’s global HMG network to assist companies who are participating in any trade mission, either NPH or national.</p><p> </p><p>We do not intend to place a map of the UK on trade show stands.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","203422","2018-12-21T15:34:29.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027712/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027712/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027712/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-12-18","Trade Fairs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 20 November 2018 to Question 19141, what assessment his Department has made of the extent to which the North East is represented by his Department's trade show stands; and if he will make it his policy to include a map of the UK in those trade show stands.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","203424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027713","Department for International Trade","false","2018-12-21","<p>The UK is party to a number of international agreements that support greater transparency and higher ethical standards in global supply chains. These include the OECD Guidelines for Multinational Enterprises, UN Guiding Principles on Business and the UN Global Compact. The government also supports initiatives led by business or NGOs such as the Corporate Human Rights Benchmark and the Fairtrade movement. The Modern Slavery Act 2015 also requires that all large businesses produce an annual statement explaining what they have done to prevent modern slavery in their business and supply chains.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-12-21T11:56:35.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027713/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027713/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027713/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-12-18","Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps the Government is taking to encourage UK businesses to increase the transparency and visibility of their global supply chains.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","203425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027714","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-20","<p>The independently chaired Clinical Priorities Advisory Group met in November 2018 to make prioritisation recommendations for investments in specialised service for the 2019/20 financial year. Final investment decisions will be announced shortly. A second prioritisation round for investment in 2019/20 will be held next year.</p><p> </p><p>The baseline budget for prioritisation in 2019/20 has been set at £25.7 million reflecting a 2.7% increase on the 2018/19 budget. The availability of any additional funding to support prioritisation will be kept under review between now and May/June 2019 when the second round of investment decisions will be taken for the 2019/20 financial year.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-12-20T15:58:15.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027714/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027714/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027714/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-12-18","Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer on 11 September to Question number 169109 on Social Care: Drugs, (a) when the 2019-20 planning process was completed and (b) what the level of funding is for the 2019-20 prioritisation process.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","203288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027715","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-20","<p>Telephone call recordings are retained for as long as there is a business requirement, this varies depending on the nature of the call.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-12-20T15:32:52.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027715/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027715/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1027715/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-12-18","Department for Work and Pensions: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how long her Department keeps its recordings of telephone conversations.","false","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","Hemel Hempstead","Sir Mike Penning","203289"
